Solve this murder mystery using only command line programs.

To figure out who-done-it, go to the 'mystery' subdirectory and start collecting all the clues from the 'crimescene' file.

The officers on the scene were super meticulous and wrote down EVERYTHING in their reports.

Fortunately, their sergeant went through and marked the real clues with the word "CLUE" in all caps.

If you get stuck, you can read the 'hint' files, which are ordered from least to most damaging.

When you think you've solved the mystery, read the 'solution' file.
